Notes:

Day 1:

1. Print statement: eg) print(“Hello World”)
2. String concatenation: eg) print(“Hello” + “ “ + “World”)
3. Input statement (To take an input): eg) input(“What is your name?”)
4. Variables(Should be one word / can’t begin with numbers) 
Eg) 
name = input(“What is your name?”)
print(name)
length = len(name) 
print(length)


Day 2:

1. Data types: String, integer, float, boolean 
2. We cannot concatenate string with an integer 
3. To check the data type: 
Eg) 
a=123
print(type(a))
4. To round a number:
Eg) 
print(round(2.6666,2))
Answer: 2.67 (Here, I rounded it to 2 decimal places)


